		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Unfortunately, this [wla] is otherwise among the best assemblers [...]</div>
<br />Hahahahahahahaha. Not my experience at all. Ignoring the crappy documentation, constant extra crap you have to add to opcodes/operands, and the awful error messages, I've found numerous bugs in several areas (even the damn preprocessor can corrupt host memory). The source is a mess to try to extend/fix. If you're doing NES development, I highly recommend ca65.

		

